@sillycibin @SNeurotypicals Neurodiversity: There is natural variation in people's brains.
Neurotypical: your brain structure fits a series of characteristics that align with the demands of society in a TYPICAL, expected way
Neurodivergent: your brain structure diverges from that typicality; is pathologized

@CosmicLoveSage Neurodiversity is referring to a variation of experience.
These variations of experience can influence the brain to operate in unique ways that diverge from what is considered the neurotypical experience.

I am not attempting to invalidate your experience.

